PSA:  Please stop asking me when I’m going to dye my grey hair. I’m not, I can not. 🤯😱

I suffered a severe reaction to it, and if I do it again, most likely it will be worse. 

I don’t mind my greys at all, it’s life and they’re beautiful. 

Remember if you’re going to chemically change your hair it’s a good idea to patch test your skin at least TWICE, and sometimes it’s still a little iffy. 

(The almost died part is a bit dramatic, but it sure felt like that way.) 
But yea, this reaction was mentally, emotionally and physically draining and if I don’t have to go through that again, I won’t. #hair #naturalhair #curlyhair #dyeallergy #hairdye #hairdyeallergy
Yep! Still loving my #dyson #dysonhair #dysonsupersonic #natural #naturalhair

I always get this question and I could lie to sell more affiliate products but I’m not that type of influencer. The truth is I’ve always had long, healthy hair. It’s genetics, my grandmother, my mother, my aunts…it’s that’s simple. 

BUT, while I may have inherited these locks, consistent and proper care have helped me to maintain my length and health. 

Washing weekly, deep conditioning, using products void of harsh chemicals, going to a professional for assessments, getting my trims and more. 

So even though I’ve always had very long hair, it’s definitely not the only way to achieve length and health. 👏🏾

I went back and forth so many times with how to wear my hair for my wedding. My gut was always “wear ya curls”, but I didn’t make up my mind until top of the year.

I did so many dry runs until I was happy with my styling products.  The two products that I decided to style my hair with were @notyourmothers Curl Talk Leave-In topped off with @innersenseorganicbeauty I-Create Hold Gel topped off with a mist of @fantasiahaircare IC hair shine spray.

I used my @dysonhair diffuser to lock my curls in place and it was perfection! 😗

@by.yashica finished off the lewk by styling and pinning my hair and clip into place. 🙏🏾 

I was 100% in LOVE with how it came out and looked. 😍

So if you come across this post, know that curly hair is FORMAL hair! Curly hair is “BUSINESS” hair! Curly hair is WEDDING hair! 👏🏾

…that’s Mrs. Munroe to you baby. 🥵

Going into the process of choosing a wedding dress I was dreading it. My style is minimalistic, elegant, a likkle old glamour and classic. 😉

I knew I wanted three things: mermaid, buttons down the back and strapless, with zerooooo bling. 

I visited 4 major stores in New York and Atlanta and at had made the decision in my mind what the dress would be. When @ngduncanson and I went to finalize details, I was not happy with my selection. I almost had a panic attack. 😭 

The week before traveling, I was randomly googling stores in Atlanta and found one store that had a particular dress I liked, when I phoned them, they didn’t have it. Just random Sherice actions….

After freaking out, and almost melting down in the bridal store where my dress was supposed to have been, I called @larainesboutique and asked if they had an appointment that same day, they did! Total shot in the dark. 

We left our current store and drove there as fast as we could (within the speed limit). As I was walking into the store, I said “that’s my dress”, the one starring at me in the window. Looka God 🙏🏾

I tried on a few dresses, just to be sure, while all looked amazing, my heart punched me in the face and said, “DIS DA ONE”. I had “the feeling”. 🥰

Courtney and the team were so amazing, inviting and efficient. The entire process was a dream. She ensured that everything was as it should be, even down to the alterations - she calmed me right down because whew chile. 🥲

So yeah, das my wedding dress story that no one asked for but y’all had to hear. 😊 Ain’t she a beauty! 🥰

Happy National Curl Day! ✨

A few major tips I’ve learned while maintaining my curls over the years. 

📌 Wash weekly (duh) 🤣
📌 Deep condition with heat. 🔥
📌 Trim ends as needed. ✂️
📌 Listen to your hair. 👂🏾

A lot of people have an emotional connection to their hair, and to others it’s just hair. Don’t allow anyone to make you feel bad about whatever side of the fence you stand on.

When I need a break, the most practical and easiest style for me is a few chunky twists! 

I use some @breadbeautysupply Hair Cream, twist and then dry a little with my @dysonhair and then gon bout my business! 

I’m not a major fan of twist outs so I barely do them, my hair just never looks right with a twist out. 🫢 I think it lacks the texture to hold…or something. 

But, yea, this is IT!

It’s the Battle of The Brushes! 🥊

Which curl definition do you prefer? The Wet Brush or The Tangle Teezer? 

It’s a personal choice but for me and my curls our preference is elongation, so we’ve been reaching more for the Tangle Teezer. 

I know both look awesome and it’s a very subtle difference, but if you’re a curl girl…you like what you like. @tangleteezer

I’m not a twist out girl, but I love the ease of twists. Not having to fumble around with hair every day is a win. Then, taking them out, another win. 😍

Styled with @breadbeautysupply Hair Cream 😍

My favourite curl combination. ❤️

These two products Not Your Your Mother’s Curl Talk Leave In + Innersense I Create Hold Gel are two of my holy grail products. 

I always know what I’m going to get with this combo and that’s why I consistently reach for them! 🙌🏾

What are my Dyson diffuser settings?  I’ve found my sweet spot to be low heat, low speed…then cranking it up to medium heat! 

This combo gives me the best results for MY hair! 🙈 

Hair length, density and styling products will account for how long your hair will take to diffuse!  Play around with your settings and find your sweet spot!

I wanted to cut my hair for quite some time but promised I’d hold off until after the wedding. I had a few stylists and salons shortlisted and decided to ultimately go with @nevila_curlystylist at the @rezosalon 

I wanted a short layered cut that would (hopefully) cut my wash time in half, cuz a girl is tired of hair! 

I was a little skeptical of not getting bangs but I didn’t want em, 🫠 they can be torture to style, but I’m still thinking about going back for some…

Also, I know I said I chatted with Nevila about the reasons you should cut hair dry and this is a summary of what she said. 

💡 Hair is cut dry to see texture of curls and so that you can see how the curls will fall, additionally the hair is in its natural state which makes for a better ✂️

💡 Also, another tip, ensure that you get your trims every 4-6 months.

While I do think the tool is sleek, and well engineered, I’m not someone who is looking for a constant straight look so this isn’t for me. However it could be for you, if that’s your vibe. 

It’s a handy tool if you’re prepping your hair for braids, or a flat iron, but it’s honestly an extra step that most likely can be achieved with a blow dryer.

The products that you use on your curly hair can make your hair look and feel different. 

Gels are my favourite because they give me ⤵️

Super defined curls , frizz free curls but you can get a curl cast which is so easy to fluff out, and of course curls that last. 

On the other hand cream stylers give you a soft hold, lots of volume but you are susceptible to more frizz, super moisturized hair and your curls may not last as long. 

It depends on your preference and which one your hair loves more. 

I love a good cream but I’m more of a gel girl 💁🏾‍♀️ #washngo #gel #curls #curlyhair #naturalhair
